reviews.review_text:
very enjoyable Always great energy at Saratoga, and this one was no exception. The audience goes nuts right out of the chute for the revived 60s arrangement of Dancin' in the Street, and it gets the band off to a great start.

Pretty good audience recording. Not A+ quality but consistent and has limited crowd intrusion. A nice listen.
